    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Keywork for the flute developed by Theobald Boehm in the 1830s, involving an improved placement of fingerholes and a key mechanism to provide full venting and bring all fingerholes within easy control of the fingers. Other instrument makers later adapted the system for the clarinet, oboe, bassoon, and other aerophones.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kleppensysteem voor de fluit, ontwikkeld door Theobald Boehm rond 1830, met een verbeterde plaatsing van vingergaatjes en een kleppenmechanisme dat volledige ventilatie mogelijk maakt en alle vingergaatjes onder gemakkelijke controle van de vingers brengt. Andere instrumentenmakers pasten het systeem later toe op de klarinet, hobo, fagot en andere aerofonen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052453/Algemene muziekencyclopedie (1961)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>長笛的按鍵系統，由提歐巴特．貝姆（Theobald Boehm）於 1830 年代所研發；旨在改良指孔位置與按鍵機械結構，可讓音質飽滿有力，並方便手指控制各個指孔。日後的其他樂器製造商也將此系統應用於單簧管、雙簧管、低音管和其他氣鳴樂器上。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Klappensystem für die Flöte, entwickelt in den 1830er Jahren von Theobald Böhm, mit einer verbesserten Platzierung der Grifflöcher und einer Klappenmechanik, die in Normalstellung offene Klappen vorsieht und alle Tonlöcher unter leichte Kontrolle der Finger bringt. Andere Instrumentenbauer wendeten das System später auf Klarinette, Oboe, Fagott und andere Aerofone an.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
